  "local_port": 36108,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some AngularJS interview questions?",
  "response": "Sure, here are some AngularJS interview questions that can help you prepare for an interview:\n\n### Basic Questions:\n1. **What is AngularJS?**\n   - Explain the main features and advantages of using AngularJS.\n\n2. **What are the key features of AngularJS?**\n   - Discuss features like two-way data binding, MVC architecture, dependency injection, directives, etc.\n\n3. **What is the difference between AngularJS and Angular?**\n   - Highlight the differences between AngularJS (version 1.x) and Angular (versions 2+).\n\n4. **What is a scope in AngularJS?**\n   - Describe the concept of scope, its types (root scope and child scope), and how scopes are used in AngularJS.\n\n### Intermediate Questions:\n5. **Can you explain the MVC architecture in AngularJS?**\n   - Discuss how AngularJS implements MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture.\n\n6. **What are directives in AngularJS?**\n   - Explain what directives are, and provide examples of built-in directives and custom directives.\n\n7. **How does data binding work in AngularJS?**\n   - Describe the different types of data binding: one-way, two-way, and one-time data binding.\n\n8. **What is dependency injection in AngularJS?**\n   - Explain the concept of dependency injection and how it is used for managing dependencies in AngularJS.\n\n9. **What are services in AngularJS?**\n   - Discuss the role of services and how they are created and used in AngularJS.\n\n10. **What is the difference between $scope and $rootScope?**\n    - Explain the differences between $scope and $rootScope and their respective roles.\n\n### Advanced Questions:\n11. **How does AngularJS handle error handling?**\n    - Describe how AngularJS manages errors and exceptions.\n\n12. **Can you explain the digest cycle in AngularJS?**\n    - Discuss the digest cycle, how it works, and its importance in AngularJS.\n\n13. **What is the purpose of ng-repeat and how does it work?**\n    - Explain the purpose of the ng-repeat directive and how it is used to iterate over collections.\n\n14. **How would you optimize the performance of an AngularJS application?**\n    - Discuss strategies for improving performance such as using $watch, one-time binding, and minimizing DOM manipulations.\n\n15. **What is the difference between $http and $resource in AngularJS?**\n    - Explain the differences between these two services and when to use each.\n\n### Practical Questions:\n16. **Can you walk through the process of creating a custom directive in AngularJS?**\n    - Provide a step-by-step explanation and example of creating a custom directive.\n\n17. **How would you handle routing in an AngularJS application?**\n    - Discuss the ngRoute module and how to configure routes.\n\n18. **What are promises in AngularJS and how do they work?**\n    - Explain the concept of promises, how they are used for asynchronous operations, and provide examples.\n\n19. **How do you test an AngularJS application?**\n    - Describe the tools and techniques used for testing AngularJS applications, such as Karma and Protractor.\n\n20. **Can you explain the concept of modules in AngularJS?**\n    - Discuss what modules are, how they are created, and their importance in structuring AngularJS applications.\n\nThese questions cover a range of topics from basic concepts to more advanced features of AngularJS. Preparing answers to these questions will help you demonstrate your understanding and expertise in AngularJS during an interview.",
